<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="71" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d71">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/11–844: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hyde
                                        Park</hi>, N.Y.</placeName>] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-08">November 8, 1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Approve French Membership on European Advisory Commission to be announced
                            November 11th, but this should be so worded as to make advisory
                            character of Commission clear.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>